news.title: Kolhapur civic body gets 206 building plans in manual mode on June 30
news.para: ​The unified rules have come into place across all civic bodies except for Mumbai, to ensure that the development takes place uniformly across the state.

news.title: Fix flaws in civic amenities in colonies taken over: Gurugram civic body commissioner
news.para: ​Commissioner Mukesh Kumar Ahuja fixed a deadline of 24 hours to resolve the problems. He has also appointed new nodal officers to oversee the services in these colonies.

news.title: Beneficiaries of housing scheme in Vijayawada sell plots
news.para: Despite guidelines against the sale of plots, around 190 beneficiaries have already sold their plots through agreements on stamp papers.

news.title: Ahmedabad most affordable housing market among top eight cities: Report
news.para: Ahmedabad is the most affordable housing market amongst the top eight cities, with a ratio of 22 per cent followed by Pune and Chennai at 26 per cent each in the first half of the calendar year 2022, the property consultant said in a statement.

news.title: In a setback for banks, UltraTech Cement drops plan to buy Jaypee Plant
news.para: The UP-based 3 million tonne plant was part of the Rs 16,189 crore acquisition of six integrated cement plants and five grinding units with a capacity of 21.2 million tonnes of the Jaypee Group by Ultratech, which was completed in 2017.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Differing rules defeat transit FSI relaxation
news.para: ​One guideline instructs the authorities to measure 200m from the centre of the road on both sides while the other says the edge of the road is to be the starting point.

news.title: Lucknow development body to revamp city infrastructure with Rs 66 crore
news.para: The priority projects are construction of slip road for Kanpur road; under-construction Pipraghat-Shaheed road along Gomti; additional pumping station worth Rs 12 crore at Gomtinagar extension; wetland and theme park under CG City for Rs 12 crore and bridge at Gaughat costing Rs 50 crore.

news.title: Chandigarh: Adviser raps officials sitting on files of property auction
news.para: Unhappy with the approach of officials keeping files of properties auction pending, UT adviser Dharam Pal has pulled them up while asserting the delay was ultimately creating hurdles in the economic growth of the city.

news.title: Property revenue collection in Maharashtra in June crosses Rs 3,000 crore
news.para: In the first quarter of this fiscal, revenue collections have registered an increase of nearly 113% as compared to the same period last year, stated registration officials.

news.title: Pune civic body, PCMC not to shift to new online system for building nods
news.para: The civic body is satisfied with its current online building permission system and will not shift to the one introduced by the state government with effect from Friday.

news.title: Wastes from mining & steel sectors can be used in cement manufacturing: Steel minister
news.para: ​Singh said that there are immense possibilities of utilisation of waste generated during mining, steel manufacturing process and end of life products, according to a steel ministry statement.

news.title: Delhi civic body extends last date for filing property tax for availing rebate to July 15
news.para: Previously, the last date was June 30. MCD provides a rebate of 15 per cent in property tax if the amount due for current financial year is paid in lump sum.

news.title: Need a month to reply to farmhouse owners' letters: Noida authority to tell court
news.para: Over 100 owners of farmhouses along the Yamuna in Sector 135 have sent their objections to the authority so far.

news.title: Thailand to extend property market support measures
news.para: The measures due to expire this year include a 100% loan-to-value ratio and reduced fees to help increase activity in the real estate sector, which officials said would take longer to recover.

news.title: PACL case: Deadline for investors to submit original investment documents extended till Aug 31
news.para: ​They are required to submit their documents only after receiving an SMS from the panel. This is applicable only for those investors whose claim money is between Rs 10,001 and Rs 15,000 and whose applications have been verified.
